{"hash":"6b998a9ef7316aa0a42beb1ba295eb05bd215169","data":{"post":{"title":"Enable IPv6 connection to AWS instances","date":"April 17 2024","content":"<p>I was planning to create an AWS instance to host my new project - Signals Talk. I noticed AWS is going to <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-aws-public-ipv4-address-charge-public-ip-insights/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">charge for public IPv4 addresses</a>. On AWS Lightsail, IPv4 instances will be <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/compute/announcing-ipv6-instance-bundles-and-pricing-update-on-amazon-lightsail/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">$2-$4 more expensive</a> than IPv6-only instances. I decided to try and get an IPv6-only instance working for my application.</p>\n<p>IPv6 only networking type is only selectable for Operation System (OS) only blueprint. So I chose Ubuntu 22.04 LTS. Also note that browser-based SSH client is not available - that means I will have to SSH from my local laptop. There‚Äôs another note: ‚ÄúAn IPv6-only instance cannot be the origin for a distribution‚Äù, which does not affect my application.</p>\n<p>After the instance is running, I tried SSH from my local:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ <span class=\"token function\">ssh</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-i</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>secret.pem<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> ubuntu@<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>ipv6_address<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>. No route to <span class=\"token function\">host</span></code></pre>\n<p>‚ÄúNo route to host‚Äù!? I wondered what that means‚Ä¶ I searched around and suspected something‚Äôs not quite right in my setup. I went to <a href=\"https://test-ipv6.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://test-ipv6.com</a> and voila - I do not have an IPv6 address!</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 2538 1164' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-1ef87a0762197f0163c7ac3d855155df'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-1ef87a0762197f0163c7ac3d855155df)' width='2538' height='1164' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAdCAYAAAAaeWr3AAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAKcklEQVR4nM1Z%2b1OU1xneREQuuwu7sDf2Asuyu%2bwCuwvsAsICCyJyUUARg6JUjKYk0XjJtTbJxExqbJIm6S%2bdmk4nqa2t1VGjVkG8pG0mmUyn/R/av6F/wNP3Od9%2bwipmWsQmPzxzznm/c85%2b33t53vecNRyYPYjLn1/Fp5%2bdwe/O/h4vHHkVvzz9OV47/j6Ov/4BPvnVFXz2m%2bvoH9qOJwtMMJe5YLQ4vhXFpfbvHfhe%2bUYLKmvq8LOPz%2bLXn15HpncQhoHhMRx98RUcOnwMh4%2b%2biOHRCezb/zJGtv4A2yb2YXrvMcw8/RLizWkUmstRUl4Bk9WZA25uslIxTtVa7J7vHax2rzKerzqCAzNHcGD2OGLN7TAEauNwV4Vhcfjk49wwyweW2FzSutSCaCIJtz%2bEmkgcHn8tKipD8MomCoGIyMKIxFJKs%2bGGZtkrhKISm%2bD7YXUaRYP0xVhmebf2wrXozjfAZ3fCEE92YPvOGUzNzKKxpRP9m8cxLuOxid2ob2zFhsFRZPo3Y9vkNJLt3Rga24GR7VPYOLxV2l0Y27EbW8Z3oXvjsFozOX1AlBFFiSjP6vB%2bZxYvtblRYC5Dgcmag3UCr8WG3nIrom4PDAWmMtjdVejs6ccmCYfR8Ul0bxhAsi0j7RakM4Po6hlCIplGunsQPRtH0N27GV29w6rN9G1BZ2ZI5KOINbWLh9TA4amGraJSUJUDO%2bHOhXrmqszOXw1Uodzpk/cIqnfM9I2od8zIt7Dd0D%2bGVOdG5Ml32yp8MKwzWsW9Yzh/4SLm529iYX5O%2bhdw6r3T%2bOP5r3H27Be4cOErvPnWhzj9yTVcvPg1zp37K86cuavaGzf%2bjjO/vYMrV/6BI8dOwGDIU%2b5Pxa4zlqlWx9qiUiFSM9YUlCg8uc4sMks2ZFYHdH3%2bjj/YgD%2bcu4vLl7/BxUtfC8H/Wb3vpUt/w6mfnkZeoRkOUZiBxOauCqKppQNNrZ1o798q/TRa2jNq3JbeIP0epGTc2tGL5Ppu8Y4upNZnFNinnH2uaZS1jakOJARNej/Zrsa9G4cwNv6UEOyEwtbtk%2bjpG0QomkBtQxNq61cPEeGj%2bkQrGiSM2dYnWhQaGtvEU9sUodtd4gHUmtNXg%2bJiM3xdE5iZ/zc8qQHUBCMIRBII1jXCH6pXjElOqJWNg/LCgdoYwvJDIXnOZyTJSDyF2lhSyeLy0c2iHMoC8swnJNnV24%2bdU3uwY3IKE5O7MLVnr4TVBmU5ZheS7uqBGcmRzVCL4NjlCygvtbu8mgIc3gCMJeUoCyTQOvserJVRlMoGJUIkJBOVRoTQ2NeJTWu9KJN408flEsv8cX0eW6ZJp%2by/aZDxJxzSt0